  "description": [
    "II EDUCATION IN THE SOVIET UNION Soviet System Struggles In Effort To Bring Education Closer To Life By DR GEORGE V KIRK i EDITORS NOTE the eighth in a series of ar ticles written especially for this paper by Dr Kirk su perintendent of Smyrna Special Schools on his re cent trip to the Soviet Un ion Questions addressed to the author concerning the trip people living condi tions etc behind the Iron Curtain my be sent to The Smyrna Times Kirk Pro ject 2527 Commerce St Smyrna Delaware In one way certainly the So viets are much like the United States The people of the Soviet Union and a number of govern ment officials have for the past few years been criticizing the educational program within the Soviet Union As you will recall the Soviet Union Education Pro gram as far as the TenYear School is concerned begins at age 7 and continues for a ten year period with a strongly aca demic program including alge bra geometry trigonometry chemistry astronomy geo graphy history foreign langu ages biology Russian language and literature for all boys and girls There is no program for those youngsters who wish to enter commercial"
